laboratory_examinations.findings: NO ANTIBODY TO B. BURGDORFERI DETECTED BY EIA. Reference Range: No antibody detected.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Negative results do not rule out B. burgdorferi infection. Patients in early stages of infection or on antibiotic therapy may not produce detectable levels of antibody.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Ultrasound of the liver or gallbladder
laboratory_examinations.findings: The liver is of normal echotexture with no focal liver lesions. The pancreas is unremarkable with homogeneous parenchyma. The common bile duct measures 5 mm with no convincing evidence of stone.
